addPlugin

public void addPlugin(File xml)
               throws edu.iastate.cs309.plugins.exceptions.PluginConflictsException,
                      edu.iastate.cs309.plugins.exceptions.PluginVersionCompatException,
                      IOException
This adds a Plugin to the system. All exceptions should be caught and displayed to the user.

Parameters:
xml - the File pointing to the xml representation of the plugin
Throws:
edu.iastate.cs309.plugins.exceptions.PluginConflictsException - if the plugin cannot be installed because of file conflicts, the message should have a list of the files that conflict
edu.iastate.cs309.plugins.exceptions.PluginVersionCompatException - if the plugin has incompatible versions, has a nice message
IOException - if files cannot be installed

uninstallPlugin

public boolean uninstallPlugin(File dir)
Uninstalls the plugin referenced by the directory.

Parameters:
dir - The directory to remove
Returns:
false if the plugin is not removed

getInstalledPlugins

public ArrayList<File> getInstalledPlugins()
Gets a list of possible plugins to uninstall. The File that is wanted to uninstall should be passed to uninstallPlugin

Returns:
a list of plugins installed.

removeAllPlugins

public static void removeAllPlugins()
This method will erase all plugins. This method should be an option for the "Safe Mode" of the program. It should be run before instantiation of the PluginManager

removeAllPluginsLocal

public boolean removeAllPluginsLocal()
Removes all plugins nicely

Returns:
true if all plugins are removed, false if there are no plugins or one of the plugins is failed to be removed
